inn1.comm: good delivery to start with, pitches it on a length and gets it to shape away from outside off stump, left alone
on target again, getting some away movement, he takes a step out and leaves it alone
this one went straight on after pitching close to off, he was forward and was struck on the pads, but outside the line
straightens this time from around off, good stuff from Thomo, bit of bounce too, defended down the track
bowls it too straight now, around middle and is picked away through midwicket
pleasing stroke, easy on the eyes, he takes a step out, and caresses the full delivery through covers, not much power on the shot though
bowls a fullish delivery angled on around off stump, he takes a half step out and drives back down the pitch, the bowler gets a hand to it
plants the front foot across the stumps, and works this one on off to  square leg
not much pace from either of the bowlers, but they have been on target though, this one on middle is driven to mid on, Ngoche was the fielder and he got some bad bounce, and a misfield results
no movement for Otieno so far, pitching it full on the stumps and is driven past the non-striker to mid on
left alone outside the off stump
good probing delivery, not full enough for the drive, not short enough for the cut, close to off stump, he was in two minds initially but let it go finally
takes it on the pads as he looks to whip it through midwicket, the ball rolls away harmlessly on the leg side
again getting that front foot forward and across, and then brings down the bat in front of pad to flick a length ball to midwicket
Odoyo's turn to bowl the probing line outside off stump, he leaves it alone wisely as two slips wait
goes wider this time outside off, and moving away after pitching around back of a length, easily left alone
gets forward to defend a length ball outside off, Odoyo gets some extra bounce that strikes him high on the bat
ooh, that was close, he had him playing across to a fullish one on the stumps, and he ended up scooping it in the air, but it fell in no man;s land just behind the non-striker's stumps
Otieno continues with the channel outside off stump, this time he got it to come in a bit from a length, left alone
more steady stuff from Otieno, he gets some extra bounce now, but its outside off and he lets it go
he is getting just a tad touchy here, yet to get off the mark, takes a step forward and across, and plays a length ball to midwicket

stayed on the back foot looking to thump him through covers, but he got a lot of bounce and he had to play it out to short extra cover, there is bounce in this track, the Pakistani seamers will love it
good tidy stuff from the Kenyans, left alone outside off
that nagging length which is not there for any shot but the forcing one, he tries to play one but short extra cover is there in the way
straightening from around off stump again, played out to point
this one died on its way to the keeper, it was left outside off stump

the first boundary of the innings arrives, and it took a different approach to achieve that, Hafeez walked across his stumps and lifted a length delivery over square leg, and it just about made the ropes
good response from the bowler, bit of extra effort, comes back in a long way from outside off, struck him on the pads, but way outside the line as he pushed forward
has him stretching out now, to a delivery pitched fuller, and he pushes to short extra cover
looks to get that big incoming delivery going again, this one does not move in as much, defended cautiously
he was standing outside off stump ages before the ball was delivered, Otieno stuck to the line outside off, and he pushed it back to the bowler in the end
he is finally off the mark off the 13th ball, getting a thick edge as he pushed at one dug in back of a length outside off

jeez, what a ripper! it was clipped neatly off the toes, and was in the gap too, but just as it was about to pass midwicket, Waters went screaming to his left horizontally, took the ball, but even as he fell it went out of his grasp, but he took it cleanly in the end with the right hand, an absolute screamer, Hafeez cannot believe it, but he has to walk back after umpteen replays confirm it was clean
bends his back and gets it to bounce from back of a length, he stays back and plays it backward of point
Kamran stays in the crease and thumps this back of a length ball off the back foot, extra cover dives and fields, but Otieno has over stepped
can't get the free hit away for much, he got behind the shortish ball, but hammered it not far away from mid off
very full on the stumps, flicked elegantly to mid on
back of a length outside off, played down the track
he is standing outside off as the ball is delivered and plays out a length ball towards mid on, this is tight stuff from Kenya
there for the cut, short and wide, but he misses out, it was gentle delivery but he could not connect
defended off the back foot towards mid off

Shehzad's stuttering stay in the middle is over, it was a length ball on off, nothing special about it, but he wanted to go midwicket, ended up going in the air straight to mid off as he got the leading edge, he had been going across the stumps, and trying to play across the line for some time now, and has paid the price ultimately
nicely on top of a length delivery close to off stump, and defends it confidently in to the off side
shuffles across and plays out a full delivery to midwicket

rare poor delivery, full toss on the stumps, helped past a diving mid on for some useful runs, if the throw had come to the non-striker's end, it wouldn't have been so useful actually, he would have been gone
remains in the crease, and plays out a length ball towards short extra cover
he angles most of his deliveries full in to the right hander, finishing around off stump, and that's what makes it tough to whip him away through midwicket, another one is defended
this time he goes middle with the angle, and it allows Younis to pick him away through square leg for a single
for the second time this over he bowls a full toss, outside off stump, and he Kamran gets forward and finds the gap past mid off for a couple

they are gifting full tosses now, another one is whipped through midwicket, slows down as it nears the boundary, and that allows the man running in from deep square leg to put in the dive and save a run
played out in to the off side
tucked away off the pads towards midwicket, cannot get the single
one more full toss, where are the Kenyan replacements, the pressure is being released, this one is flicked past square leg
Odoyo is losing it here, now he bowls a short one that goes way down leg
short again, but the line is on middle, and he defends off the back foot
yet another full toss, this time he misses out, and drives it straight to mid on
he is welcomed with a straight drive past the non-striker, it was a half volley and Younis capitalised, getting the placement perfect, and also gets a no-ball as Odhiambo oversteps by a huge margin
gives it a heave, but it was a slower ball on target, and he could only hit it to deepish mid off
he is looking good here Younis, gets quickly on the back foot and steers a length ball to third man
Kamran looks to do the same, steer that is, but this one is very close to the body, and he chops it on the crease, one more no-ball
gets a short one, and sends it screaming over the square leg umpire for a boundary, and Odhiambo has overstepped again, he has wasted whatever the opening bowlers managed to do
not a no-ball this time, but it is a hit-me full toss, and Kamran hammers it over the bowler in a flash
finally gets one on target, in the channel outside off stump, he lets it go
gets well forward to a length delivery and plays it out to point
goes stretching forward again, and pushes out this one again to point
he is right on the money, bowling one full on off stump, he goes across to drive it to mid on
gets an inside edge as he looks to whip this angled delivery, and it scoots away in front of square leg
full again, this time outside off stump, driven down to mid off
he is keeping it consistently full on the stumps, Kamran cannot get timing on the drive, sends the ball to mid on
not short enough, but Kamran is game for the cut, and gets it to deep point for a couple
reverts to the full length again, and is pushed past the non-striker;s stumps for a single
pacy delivery dug in short of a length, played back to the bowler
times the punch really well, but hits it straight to extra cover,. who is right on the edge of the circle
Kamran gets innovative, and very effective too, goes across and outside the off stump to pick a length delivery over midwicket, he got the swing and the connection just right
gets forward confidently and drives this length ball towards cover
another lovely drive, getting to the pitch in an instant, and pinging mid off with a powerful drive
as free flowing as possible, opens the bat face to drive a length ball to cover, oh if elegance could get runs, Kamran would have had 12 for those three shots
very full, almost in the blockhole, his bat turns in his hands and he plays it out towards midwicket
top shot from Younis, stretched forward and got the placement between cover and extra cover
surprises him with the short one, got big on him, he was going forward already, hastily backtracked and fended it on the leg side,  it was in the air for a while but there was no one there
stays back and works one away through square leg
that was the perfect one-day delivery, just around back of a length, finishing on off stump, no room to do anything but defend, which Younis does crisply
confident stride forward and dead bats a length ball towards the covers
lovely placement from Kamran, got some width outside off stump, and just went through with the shot, driving on the up past point, and wide of third man who saw it clatter into the boundary
full outside off stump, gets forward and drives to mid off
remains in the crease and lets this one comes in and hit his broad defensive blade
gets away with a full toss, it was worked away wide of mid on but he was quick to get to it, and put in the dive to save the boundary
gets an inside edge as he whips this fullish ball which goes backward of square leg
gets forward and plays out a length ball with an open face to point
lets a length ball come on outside off and guides it to point, thought about a single for a moment, only a fleeting moment
wide outside off stump and slashed away to a squarish third man
goes back to a short of a length ball and looks to tap it into covers but it goes straight to the fielder
good fielding  at mid off, it was driven sweetly but he dived to his right to save a few
a bouncer from Kenya, there haven;t been many of those, Kamran goes down underneath it, there is a man at deep square leg
this time his straight drive is so straight that mid off had no chance, dive or whatever, mid on gives chase to haul it back in
defends a full pitched delivery in to the off side
too straight, Younis flicks it to deep square leg to bring up the 50 of the partnership
Odhiambo goes down leg with the short ball, put in the effort, but lost the radar
rides the bounce on this one and punches it on his toes to point
looked to come forward, found the ball wasn't full enough and went back to punch it again to point
stays a bit low outside off stump, he adjusts to hit it away to sweeper cover
nicely done by Younis, went forward and tapped a length ball towards extra cover to scamper through for a run
good loopy delivery, bit of turn from off stump, played out towards extra cover
flights it fuller, he uses the wrists to work it square on the leg side
head on top of the tossed up delivery as he comes forward and defends in to the off side
paddles a full delivery on middle stump, can be dangerous but he got this one alright to fine leg
tossed up teasingly outside off stump, Yonis drives it all along the ground to sweeper cover
short and turning away, sweeper cover is in business again as Kamran cuts this one away
short outside off and not much turn, easily cut away wide of sweeper cover
closer to off stump and flighted too, he defends it calmly
hit down to long on this time
bit of turn and some bounce too, he is surprised as he keeps it down in to the leg side
bounce again, but this one is short outside off stump, he goes for the slash and gets it fine on the off side, this outfield is huge, and the fielder pulls it back inside the ropes after a long chase
full on  leg stump, helped down to long on for a run
flighted generously, comes down almost in the blockhole, he waits and then digs it out to long off
flatter this time, and driven to sweeper cover
hurries on after pitching on middle stump, he backs away outside leg and cuts it to point, got the bat down just in time
Ngoche saves a single, dives to his left and cuts off the drive down the ground
comes forward and plays this one back to the bowler
ending up on leg stump, and whipped away backward of square leg
sprays this full delivery way down the leg side
played out to square leg off the back foot
gets some time as the shortish one spins in, and punches it down to long on
take a step forward, tap the ball in front of point, and take the single, neatly done
Kamande goes down the leg side again, this time Younis takes toll, sweeps him backward of square leg, just helped it on its way
better stuff, around off stump, defended off the front foot
comes forward and drives this slow flighted one to midwicket
takes this from the fourth stump, and late cuts it past backward point, how deft is that
goes back and plays this one out towards covers
good flight on this one, he comes forward and drives it back to the bowler
too much leg side on that one, helped away to fine leg on one knee
still more flight, he seems to have a heart alright, driven to wide mid off on the front foot
another full and tossed up delivery played out towards extra cover
he is getting a lot of runs behind point, waited for a full one to arrive outside off and squeezed it past backward point
loud appeal from Kamande, but that one was going down leg, he was struck on the pads as he looked to whip it through midwicket
driven past extra cover for a single
pings long off with the drive, got to the pitch of this flighted delivery nicely
waits till the last instant, and guided this full delivery to the right of backward point
Pakistan take six off the over in efficient riskless fashion, another one is driven to long on
pushes this tossed up ball back to Ngoche
bowled slowly through the air, but a touch short and allows him to rock back and cut wide of sweeper cover
flighted on middle stump, nice control from the bowler, driven down the track
another tossed up delivery, now outside off stump, he drives to wide long off
went for a cute fine sweep, it was very full and he missed, and the ball just about went past leg stump
misses out on the short ball, hitting it straight to extra cover
pinches a quick run with a tap behind point
steered to backward point off the back foot
gets to his half-century with a punch off the back foot down to long on, he has led the recovery after the openers went nowhere
another single down to long on, is there a count of how many times that happens in ODIs?
goes for a heave-ho to a tossed up delivery outside off stump, and misses
now he goes for the cut to a flat one turning in from outside off stump, and is beaten again
this time he connects, poor ball down the leg side deservedly helped away fine for a boundary
takes a tossed up delivery on the half volley and limbers for a single as the ball goes to long off
takes this one right off middle stump, as he leans back and cuts away to sweeper cover
Odoyo at long off is being kept busy with all these singles down the ground

dear me, Kamran has lost it here, went charging blindly down the track to a tossed up delivery, and decided to swing it out of sight, but the ball turned past his flailing blade and Ouma did the rest, what a shame, he had batted so well, brain fade really, Ngoche is rewarded for flighting the ball
flighted delivery full on the leg stump, played out tentatively to midwicket
skids on after pitching and was going for middle stump, but Misbah got the bat down at the last instant to push it out towards mid on
hammers this full one to long off, free hit coming up as Tikolo over steps
Misbah is away on his World Cup debut, got one in the slot, went down on a knee and swung it straight down the ground for maximum
dropped this one went straight through outside off and Misbah got a feather on it but Ouma clanged it,
played out towards midwicket
goes for the reverse sweep now, but misses, got just a glove on it
nurdled to short fine leg
stretches forward and pushes this one in the air, but past the reach of the bowler, this is tentative from Misbah
another reverse sweep, he connects this time, and gets it past backward point for a couple
short, poor delivery, he pulls it over midwicket but there is a man on the deep boundary there
leans out and pushes this one past the bowler towards long off
more short stuff and more pulling from Misbah, deep midwicket keeps them down to one
punched hard, but Kamande prevents the single with a diving stop running to his right from extra cover
down the pads, flicked away to short fine leg
driven powerfully, and the almost-mandatory single to long on results
flighted stiff from Kamande, he pings long on with the drive again
stays back and works this one away backward of square leg
eases into an elegant drive and finds long on
now Misbah goes back to a shortish one, and punches hard down the ground, singles, singles, all around
tight delivery around off stump, defended calmly
going forward and smothering the turn on this one outside off
super running, it was nurdled backward of square leg, and by the time the man running in from the boundary got there, they hared back for two
goes back and punches this turning one back to the bowler
the reverse sweep off a full delivery, Misbah has been trying that shot constantly, backward point helps by diving over the ball
the conventional sweep now, the ball bounds away backward of square leg
down to long off for yet another run, now, now if accumulation could come across as elegant, but unfortunately it doesn't
stretches forward and pushes this flattish one past the bowler to long off
worked past midwicket for a single
driven down the track, old man Tikolo dives to his right and saves the single
makes room outside leg and cuts this short delivery past extra cover for a couple
made space again, but this time there was no room for the cut, no problem he managed to somehow hit it past the bowler
rolls away in front of square as he looks to steal another single, not this time though
worked away off the pads through square leg
shapes for the pull, the ball hurries on and he pushes out to mid on in the end
this one is asking to be pulled alright, and he does, going back and tonking it over midwicket and in to the boundary
reverse sweeps a full delivery from off stump, and it is wide enough of backward point for a couple
punched off the back foot, the bowler tries, extra cover tries, but it is left to long off to tidy up
flat and hurrying on, whipped to the right of midwicket in a flash
leans out and plays this one to midwicket
gets into a complete tangle now, as he looks to work this one to midwicket, but takes it on the body
defended in to the leg side
cannot beat a running midwicket with the back foot punch
tossed up delivery played back to the bowler
driven in the air past extra cover, shouts of 'catch him' but it is safe
goes down on a knee and sweeps this full delivery wide of fine leg, but they'll get only one
makes room for the cut, but this one is not short enough and he adjusts to play it to point
flicked away through square leg off the pads
played out to midwicket off the back foot
Ngoche gets in the way of the back foot punch down the ground and saves the single
he tries it again, but this time the drive to long off is too quick for his dive
worked away through square leg, and Pakistan are away after drinks
lunges out but plays this one out to midwicket
goes for a full-blooded sweep this time, and it goes on the bounce to deep square leg who misfields, and Younis Khan has gone to 50

Younis goes for the review, he was struck on the pads as he went for another sweep, Tikolo asked the question twice, umpire Llong gave him out after a lot of thought and replays show the ball hitting the leg stump, Pakistan lose a review, and Younis has to walk back, one more well-set batsman falls at the wrong time for Pakistan
goes forward and plays this one with the turn to square leg
Umar is away, rocks back and cuts this one away past extra cover
and with the keeper standing up, he bowls this one two feet down the legside, and the ball runs away fine in to the boundary
as if on cue, Odoyo pitches this one in the corridor outside off stump, and it is left alone
no, no, he has not taken any cue, another one sprayed wildly down leg, Ouma had no chance even from his position standing back
oops, Odoyo is giving Ouma a torrid time, this one rolls away outside the off stump to him, and he takes it with some discomfort
short of a good length, but leg side again, worked away to fine leg gleefully
gives him the short one, he tries to get on top of it and pull it but hits it to mid on on the end
good running from Umar, he worked this one in front of fine leg and set off, Misbah was hesitant but two was always on Umar's mind
yikes, this one dies under Umar's attempted cut which then turned into a flail as he saw the ball hardly bouncing but it still went under his bat
i have lost count of the number of times Misbah has played the reverse sweep today, he connects nicely again, and gets it past backward point, takes it from a very full length from off stump
lifts this one in the air but safely over midwicket, hugely optimistic shouts of 'catch it'
flights this one up, but he waits on it and drives it to long off in the end
defended in to the on side
goes back in the crease and guides this one backward of point
nicely driven down to long on, high elbow and all the jazz
sprayed wide down the leg side, Ouma is having a torrid time
played out to point off the back foot
steered very late off the back foot towards short third man
plays this tossed up delivery with the turn, but cannot get it past midwicket
turning down the pads, whipped past backward square leg
stays on the back foot, and punches this shortish ball down to long on
gets well forward to ping long off with the drive
slapped away off the back foot, just got some width, went back in a flash, and got the shot in the gap
eagerly gets forward and turns this one to midwicket
tapped with soft hands behind the wickets on the off side, and they go through for the run
eased past square leg off the front foot
gets forward and defends down the track
another tap-and-run in to the off side, good running, Misbah was off the blocks quickly
pulled away, it was not short enough, but he latched on to it in a flash and got it past midwicket
he keeps playing the reverse sweep, this ball was a touch short, he let it come on and got it past short third man
take that! Umar is so quick to pick on anything marginally short, thumps this one high and in to the gap between long on and deep midwicket, both of whom had no chance
another single brings Misbah on strike
pushed to long off for a run
stretches forward but he bowls it flat and quick, and he has to block it on the off side
the Kenyans are getting a bit ragged on the field as midwicket lets through a single
played back to the bowler
plays a cute late dab to short third man, the single was on, but was amde easier by the fact that there was another misfield
goes for another reverse sweep, by the time he looked down the track, Umar was rushing across and he sent him back hastily
slow tossed up delivery, played out in to the on side
whips this one away off the pads
flat delivery, he eases it down the ground to long off
the sweep again, this time the conventional one, takes it from middle and gets it behind square leg
high full toss, he comes down charging down at it, but swings it away to sweeper cover
misses out on a sweep this time and is struck high on the pads
one more full toss, but Misbah finds deep midwicket this time
gets forward and meets the ball with a straight bat and sends it purring down to long off
goes back and throws everything in to the pull shot, but finds deep midwicket and is not pleased with that
kept low, on the stumps too, he adjusted to push it in to the leg side
smashed down to long off, he'll get only a single for all that effort

they go upstairs to find out whether Umar had dragged his foot outside the crease as he was beaten on an attempted drive, but even as Ouma whipped off the bails, Umar's foot never left the crease, and he is absolutely safe
slow delivery turning even more slowly, he blocks it off the front foot
no pace to work with at all, Umar plays out this one in to the off side
goes back and slaps it away to sweeper cover to bring up an efficient half-century
Umar gets away with this, he was beaten in the flight and was way outside the crease, but Ouma messed up the stumping and Umar survives
gets to the pitch of this flighted one and drives it to long off
played down to long off
cannot get another tossed up delivery past the bowler, courageous stuff from Obuya at this stage of the innings
gives him a full toss and he hammers it wide of sweeper cover for a couple
full delivery on the pads, spirited away to deep square leg
gets a full delivery, makes some room outside leg stump, and drives it through covers, the ball stopped inside the boundary, and Umar did not want the third
good start to the Powerplay, backed away a shade outside leg the bowler followed him, but he adjusted to pull it all the way over square leg, got the connection absolutely at the right moment
nice response from the bowler, right in the blockhole, dug out down the track
walks across and outside off stump to whip a full delivery past square leg
he made some more room again, but Odhiambo followed with a smart slower one, and he hit it in the air in the end, but it dropped well short of extra cover
he is getting a little predictable with that backing away outside leg stuff, the bowler followed him, and fired one in the blockhole, it is dug out in to the off side
effective from Umar, planted the front foot outside off, bent the knee and lapped the full toss over short fine leg
another boundary, gets a short one outside off stump, waits for an instant to get the cut in the gap between point and cover
poor bowling this is, high full toss outside off stump, and bashed away over extra cover, flat-batted, and it went fast and flat
this is superb batting from Umar, he had backed away far outside leg, was surprised initially with the slower one that tucked him up, but played a late steer past short third man
Otieno has lost it completely, serves up a very high full toss way outside off stump, and it is clattered over the infield effortlessly
misses out on one, it was a fullish one around off stump, he made room and got bat to ball, but found the bowler in the way

now that is what is a stolen single, Misbah was tucked up with a yorker, had no clue where the ball went, but Umar hustled him in to the single, and got there just in time even as Odhiambo reached the ball
umar gets to his 50 in quick time with another deft shot, waited on the ball before cutting it backward of point for a boundary
gets the front leg out of the way, and smashes a full delivery down to long on, that will be the 100 of the stand, in 72 balls
murders a full toss on middle and leg, but straight to deep midwicket
shapes up for the fine lap shot past fine leg from outside off stump, but it is too full and he cannot get it away
goes down on one knee after backing away way down the leg side, and slogs this full delivery towards midwicket off the bottom half of the bat, shades of the Misbah of old
tucks him up with a full delivery outside leg as he made room but he still got it down to long on who lost the ball initially which allowed them to sneak two
hares down the track, and swings hard, it helps during these late stages, the outside edge goes wide of short third man who runs it all the way to the boundary in the end
what a shot! made some room outside leg, got to the pitch of a tossed up ball, and lifted it cleanly over extra cover, so cleanly that it carries all the way
comes down the track, is hit on the pads, but they still steal a single
how many of those have Kenya gifted away? it was a poor delivery way down the leg side, and short fine leg had to give it a long chase to pull it back

Misbah goes this time, swinging a full delivery straight to long on, the boundaries here are very long and he picked out the man almost to perfection, well, he's put Pakistan in a strong position though
yet another wayward one down the leg side
Boom Boom is away, gets one full and in his slot as he backs away outside leg, and lifts it straight down the ground, bounces just inside the boundary
another full delivery lifted straight down the ground, they keep backing away, and even as the bowlers try to cramp them for room, they keep connecting
whipped away to deep square leg off the pads
gets a high full toss, and no violence from the marauder, just uses the wrists to turn it to short fine leg
another one down the leg side, lifted over square leg, they take two even as Odoyo lets rip with the throw, and holds his arm immediately
pinches a single with a push into the off side
looks to go downtown, but sees the ball is shortish and calmly pushes it in to the vacant midwicket area, and they actually trot through for a couple, one of the calmest twos ever I tell you
slashes a full delivery wide of sweeper cover
picks out long on, it was the slower one, he got too much underneath the ball, but still went through with the shot, and managed to find long on in the end, what a knock though

whoops this one looked very close, it was very full too, and rapped him on the pads as he swung across the line from the crease, Odoyo's confident appeal was turned down initially, Kenya go for the referral, that is hitting middle of middle, and he will have to walk back
if that is the hattrick ball, it certainly wasnt going to get him one, it was sprayed wide down the leg side, and Ouma had no chance standing up to the stumps
full and going across the left-hander, driven hard to extra cover on the edge of the circe
keeping it very full, Razzaq goes down on a knee and drives it down to sweeper cover
and with that angle the ball goes down the leg side again, just stopped inside the ropes
short and wide, the over ends now finally, with a slap to sweeper cover off the back foot
makes some room outside leg and drives a full delivery to midwicket
you know that, extra could have a half-century of its own as well, another horrible delivery wide down leg, and runs away for loads of wides
gives it the good old thump from outside leg stump, and it falls well short of long on
cannot get the full toss past point, it was timed sweetly but straight to that man
slower one, but short enough for him to pull it past midwicket, long on does well in the end to stop it with a slide
Razzaq launches into a dismissive pull over midwicket, and sends the ball speeding in to the boundary
ouch, a high bouncer, too high in fact, Kenya's woes have overflowed
finishes off with one that rolls away to the keeper past off stump, Razzaq misses out on it, but Pakistan have played it their way in this innings, and it has served them so well

inn2.comm: lands it on a good length outside off, pushed out to mid-off
homing in on the middle stump line, tapped to the on side for a quick single
in the zone outside off stump and seams away late, the batsman is beaten, pushing inside the line
screamer! Another one firing through the off-stump channel, Waters loses his serenity and is beaten, flirting with it
And again! Oh boy, is Shoaib on fire or what? Another one that straightens outside off and again Waters doesn't get behind the line
Much better this time from Waters. He moves towards the line of the ball, covers his off stump and shoulders arms. Early nerves
full length delivery around off, driven straight to mid-off where Shahid Afridi makes a mess of a regulation stop.
